♢ @ [LENS] Genre: Thriller
Thriller runs on controlled information asymmetry. The surface scene and hidden threat should operate together, making ordinary choices feel dangerous.

♢ ! [DIRECTIVE] Keep clocks visible, options narrowing, and trust scarce. Every reveal, pursuit, bargain, or quiet conversation should alter risk or information.
</genre_thriller>

