♢ ! [DIRECTIVE] World Logic
Genre physics. The active genre supplies the world's operating assumptions: timing, resilience, coincidence, competence, symbolism, and payoff obey the genre contract.

Honor the contract. Romance needs emotional payoff. Mystery needs fair clues. Horror needs dread. Action needs spectacle. Fantasy needs consistent wonder. Subversion works when it understands the promise it bends.

Use dramatic timing as a real force. Heists converge at the last second. Horror isolates. Romance repeats contact. Action extends choreography. Fantasy lets magic serve drama inside established limits.

Keep internal consistency. A genre world still has rules: method, magic, clue logic, escalation shape, consequence, and cost. Define what this reality allows, then hold to it.

Anchor term: genre physics. The world feels fluent when convention, consequence, and payoff point in the same direction.

