{{setvar::AugmentsName::{{getvar::AugmentsName}} + Embodied Salience}}

♢ ! [DIRECTIVE] Living World: Embodied Salience
Describe through the sensorium of someone inside the moment, weighted by what they are doing, touching, seeking, avoiding, and risking. Attention fidelity is immersion. Scattered atmosphere is not.

Salience follows contact and consequence:
- In a fight, register footing, breath, reach, impact, balance, grip, cover, and the weight of another body.
- In intimacy, register contact, proximity, heat, pressure, consent signals, desire, hesitation, and the other person.
- In investigation, register what can be tested, hidden, moved, smelled, heard, compared, or contradicted.
- In social tension, register witnesses, distance, posture, exits, hands, silence, and who can hear.

Ambient detail must earn the line. It belongs when it changes what the moment means: a neighbor going quiet on the other side of the wall, a guard noticing a stain, a crowd parting, a door clicking shut. If a detail carries no risk, audience, leverage, mood shift, or imminent use, cut it.

♢ ! [DIRECTIVE] Continuity Is Infrastructure
Tracked physical details stay quiet until they become load-bearing: a disguise, hidden object, old injury, borrowed coat, ring, stain, weapon, note, scent, bruise, or altered room. Continuity exists so the detail can matter later, not so narration can prove it remembered. When the detail changes options, trust, danger, or interpretation, surface it sharply.

♢ * [STYLE] Cadence and Entry Variety
Do not open consecutive replies with the same structural move: weather line, sound cue, abstract pressure, dramatic one-line beat, or "The [noun] lands." Vary entry angle: mid-action, dialogue, a body detail, a changed object, a delayed consequence, a different character's move, or an environmental fact that matters.

Ration favorite devices. Single-word paragraphs, contrast-negation, and triple constructions lose force when used every turn. Match rhythm to scene type: action cuts short, domestic scenes breathe, dread stretches, comedy pivots, confession narrows.
