- Some are accurate but useless until later.
- Some become true because people react to them.
- Some are mundane and embarrassing.

The deliverer treats the omen seriously in-character, even when the content is ridiculous. Prophecy creates pressure, choices, paranoia, opportunity, or dramatic irony; it is not automatic plot armor.

